<!-- ============================== 1. WHAT CHANGED SINCE THE LAST REPORT ============================== -->
<h2>1. What changed since the 2026-05-18 platform report</h2>

<p>Before mapping the three improvement plans onto the codebase, the picture must be re-anchored: <b>two large commits landed</b>
after the previous report was filed, and they have already closed many of the items the plans flag.</p>

<table>
<tr><th>Commit</th><th>Date</th><th>What landed</th></tr>
<tr>
  <td><code>8d34329</code></td>
  <td>2026-05-18</td>
  <td>Launch-hardening mega-commit. <b>RSS full-body extraction</b> (BeautifulSoup + timeout + summary fallback) shipped in <code>rss_adapter.py:_parse_feed</code>. <b><code>is_synthetic = FALSE</code> filter</b> applied to 60+ user-facing SELECTs across 13 route files. <b>Sustainability v2</b> with ND-GAIN wired in (weights 0.35 / 0.30 / 0.20 / 0.15). <b>Calibration <code>is_preview</code></b> tag when <code>n_labels &lt; 50</code>. <b>Hallucination-rates schema fix</b> (<code>articles.id</code> &rarr; <code>article_id</code>). <b>Scheduler fail-closed</b> + CSP header + <code>/terms</code> + <code>/privacy</code>. 196 country codes via Google News RSS (migration 026). 658 articles enriched.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td><code>4699a70</code></td>
  <td>2026-05-19</td>
  <td>Tier-1 analytical remediations. <b>Sustainability v2</b> now adds <b>UNFCCC NDC</b> as the 5th component (weights 0.30 / 0.25 / 0.20 / 0.15 / 0.10); <b>year_spread</b> confidence-band widening (mixed-year inputs now penalised). <b>Multi-LLM numeric grounding</b> via optional callable in <code>multi_llm_verifier.py</code>; <b><code>numbers_in_claim</code></b> and <b><code>numeric_grounded</code></b> fields on <code>CorroboratedClaim</code>; corroborated-but-ungrounded claims now lose 50% confidence. <b>spaCy NER hallucination</b> entity check (graceful fallback to regex). <b>UI/UX</b>: <code>/search</code> skeleton grid, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code> landmark on article detail, <code>aria-label</code> on icon-only buttons. 477 tests passing.</td>
</tr>
</table>

<div class=callout>
<b>Honest re-grading after these two commits.</b> Of the 11 Tier-A "credibility-floor" remediations in the strategic-analysis report, <span class="done">8 are now shipped</span> and the audited composite has moved from ~3.6 toward an estimated <span class="kpi">~4.0&ndash;4.15/5</span> (still well short of the 4.78 self-claim, but materially closer). The three reports were filed against the pre-launch code; this synthesis re-reads them against HEAD.
</div>

<!-- ============================== 2. CONSENSUS / DIVERGENCE ============================== -->
<h2>2. Where the three reports agree &mdash; and where they don't</h2>

<p>Each report comes from a distinct vantage point. Their overlap is the highest-confidence backlog; their divergence reveals which strategic bet the platform should choose deliberately.</p>

<h3>2.1 Three-way consensus (high-confidence backlog)</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Recommendation</th><th>Strategic (5-tier)</th><th>Greenwashing-NLP</th><th>FAIR / dMRV</th><th>Status in code (HEAD <code>4699a70</code>)</th></tr>
<tr><td>Replace 8-publisher venue whitelist with DB-backed tiers</td><td>C2</td><td>&sect;5.3</td><td>Gap 1</td><td><span class="open">Still open</span> &mdash; <code>bayesian_credibility.py:48</code> hard-codes <code>KNOWN_VENUES</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Agentic chat actions / tool-use protocol</td><td>B2</td><td>&sect;7.1</td><td>(implicit, role-based dashboards)</td><td><span class="open">Still open</span> &mdash; no <code>actions</code> payload in <code>api/chat_routes.py</code> or <code>conversation_engine.py</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>NER + numeric grounding for hallucination/verification</td><td>B4</td><td>&sect;3.3, 5.3</td><td>Gap 5</td><td><span class="done">Done</span> &mdash; <code>4699a70</code> shipped both (numeric_grounded + spaCy)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Sustainability composite v2 (consume all 6 adapters)</td><td>B5</td><td>&sect;5.3</td><td>Gap 1</td><td><span class="done">Largely done</span> &mdash; 5 of 6 components live (IRENA still unused; needs population normaliser)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Corporate-claim verification module (CDP / SBTi / NZT)</td><td>B3</td><td>&sect;1, 6, 7</td><td>Gap 7</td><td><span class="open">Not started</span> &mdash; zero matches for <code>company_climate</code> / <code>cdp</code> / <code>sbti</code> in <code>src/backend/</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Transparent uncertainty / confidence intervals in UI</td><td>5.2 (decomposed gauge)</td><td>&sect;3.2 (LLM scoring rigour)</td><td>Gap 5 + Tier 1 #3</td><td><span class="open">Partial</span> &mdash; <code>DecomposedConfidenceChart</code> exists but is unused; gauge still a single 0&ndash;100 dial</td></tr>
<tr><td>Article-trail join: UUIDs &rarr; titles/URLs</td><td>5.3 (chat reasoning)</td><td>&sect;6.1</td><td>Tier 1 #1</td><td><span class="open">Open</span> &mdash; <code>/api/methodology/audit-trail/*</code> still returns opaque UUIDs</td></tr>
<tr><td>Calibration: raise <code>min_labels</code>, surface <code>is_preview</code></td><td>A3</td><td>&sect;5.3</td><td>Tier 1 #3</td><td><span class="done">Done</span> &mdash; <code>STABLE_FIT_MIN=50</code> on <code>RefitResult.as_dict</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>RSS full-body extraction</td><td>A1</td><td>&sect;5.3</td><td>(quality input pre-req)</td><td><span class="done">Done</span> &mdash; <code>rss_adapter.py:_parse_feed</code> fetches + extracts</td></tr>
<tr><td>Frontend filter on <code>is_synthetic = FALSE</code></td><td>A2</td><td>&sect;5.3</td><td>(integrity pre-req)</td><td><span class="done">Done</span> &mdash; 60+ API SELECTs filter; user surfaces clean</td></tr>
</table>

<h3>2.2 Where the three diverge (the strategic choice)</h3>
<table>
<tr><th>Vector</th><th>Strategic (5-tier)</th><th>Greenwashing-NLP</th><th>FAIR / dMRV</th></tr>
<tr><td><b>What the platform <i>is</i></b></td><td>Regulatory-aligned trust infrastructure for European ECGT / AI Act window</td><td>Algorithmic assurance engine grading public greenwashing</td><td>Universal trust layer / data commons with cryptographic provenance</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Largest moat to build</b></td><td>Corporate-claim verification + AI Act labelling</td><td>Adversarial multi-LLM verifier with auditor-persona prompts</td><td>Immutable audit ledger + FAIR metadata + federated mesh</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Differentiating signal</b></td><td>Published methodology standard (CFRS)</td><td>NLP detection of greenwashing patterns (vague modifiers, future-tense uncommitted targets)</td><td>Blockchain anchoring via Hyperledger / CAD Trust integration</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Defining UX move</b></td><td>Decomposed credibility gauge + persistent trust ribbon + reproduce-button</td><td>Active agentic chat that <i>shows its reasoning</i></td><td>Confidence-interval display + verification badges (&#10004; / &#10004;&#10004; / &#10004;&#10004;&#10004;) + change-provenance log</td></tr>
<tr><td><b>Long-horizon expansion</b></td><td>SKUs: Claim Substantiation + CSRD Companion</td><td>Video pipeline for verified-fact dissemination</td><td>Nature/biodiversity, dMRV certification, federated mesh, role-based dashboards, Global South PWA</td></tr>
</table>

<div class=warn>
<b>The three reports do not contradict each other &mdash; but they cannot all be the next sprint.</b>
The strategic-analysis report is fastest to monetise (ECGT window is September 2026). The FAIR/dMRV report is the largest <i>category-defining</i> bet (universal trust layer). The greenwashing-NLP report is the most defensible <i>technical</i> moat (adversarial verifier). Pick the order deliberately; do not blend the headlines.
</div>

