<!-- ============================== 4. DEEP DIVE PER RECOMMENDATION ============================== -->
<h2>4. Deep dive: implementation + impact radius</h2>

<p>Each item below carries the same four-block structure: <b>what to do</b>, <b>impact graph</b> (the files / modules touched, ready to drop into gitnexus), <b>effects</b> (capability, grade-axis lift, regulatory fit), <b>risk + rollback</b>. Items are ordered by the recommended sequence in &sect;5.</p>

<!-- =================== R1 SOURCE TIER DB =================== -->
<h3>R1. Source-tier database (replace 8-publisher whitelist)</h3>
<p><b>What.</b> Replace the hard-coded <code>KNOWN_VENUES</code> set in <code>bayesian_credibility.py:48</code> with a database-backed <code>source_credibility_tiers</code> table seeded from objective scientometric data. Tiered prior:
Tier 1 = +30 (Scimago Q1 + IFCN-verified), Tier 2 = +15 (Q2 / mainstream press with correction policy), Tier 3 = +5 (Q3&ndash;Q4 / NGO with sourcing), Unknown = 0, Retraction-flagged = &minus;30.</p>

<h4>Impact graph</h4>
<table class=impact>
<tr class=r-blast-med><td><b>Primary edit</b></td><td><code>src/backend/app/domains/intelligence/bayesian_credibility.py</code> (replace constant lookup with DB read; add LRU cache)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Schema</td><td>New migration <code>027_source_credibility_tiers.sql</code> &rarr; <code>source_credibility_tiers(source_id, domain, doi_prefix, tier, evidence_url, last_audited_at, retracted_count)</code> + seed loader script</td></tr>
<tr><td>New module</td><td><code>src/backend/app/domains/trust/source_tier_service.py</code> + <code>scripts/seed_source_tiers.py</code> (Scimago JR CSV import + RetractionWatch API integration)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Callers (already there)</td><td><code>url_analysis_routes.py</code> (compute_research_prior), <code>article_enrichment_service.py</code>, <code>provenance.py</code> (records the resolved tier into <code>claim_provenance.raw_metadata.source_tier</code>)</td></tr>
<tr><td>API surface</td><td><code>api/methodology_routes.py</code> &rarr; new <code>GET /api/methodology/source-tiers</code> + <code>GET /api/methodology/source-tier/by-domain?d=&hellip;</code> (transparency)</td></tr>
<tr><td>Frontend</td><td><code>MethodologyDrawer.tsx</code> &mdash; new "Source tier" section; <code>SourceProfileCard.tsx</code> &mdash; badge; <code>ArticleCard.tsx</code> hover state</td></tr>
<tr><td>Tests</td><td><code>tests/api/test_bayesian_credibility.py</code> (refit existing), new <code>tests/api/test_source_tier_service.py</code> + fixture CSV</td></tr>
<tr><td>Ops</td><td>Add to nightly Celery beat: <code>refresh-retraction-flags</code> (RetractionWatch RSS poll)</td></tr>
</table>

<div class=dag>
gitnexus query (when available):
  graph trace --from bayesian_credibility.py:KNOWN_VENUES --depth 4
expected fan-out: 6 backend modules, 3 routes, 1 migration, 2 frontend components, 4 tests
risk class:       MEDIUM (low blast, but the prior enters every reliability score)
</div>

<h4>Effects</h4>
<ul>
  <li>Reliability axis lift: <b>3.5 &rarr; 4.5</b> (closes the audit's largest single gap).</li>
  <li>Regulatory fit: directly satisfies ECGT &sect;Art 3 ("recognised certification schemes") and CSRD assurance-readiness.</li>
  <li>Composite grade: <b>+0.15 to +0.20</b>.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Risk &amp; rollback</h4>
<p>Risk: <b>medium</b>. The tier is multiplicative on every credibility score; a bad seed can shift the score distribution platform-wide. Rollback: env flag <code>CLILENS_USE_SOURCE_TIER_DB=false</code> falls back to the legacy whitelist. Ship behind the flag for one week of A/B before flipping.</p>

<!-- =================== R2 AGENTIC ACTIONS =================== -->
<h3>R2. Agentic chat <code>actions[]</code> protocol + client dispatchers</h3>
<p><b>What.</b> Backend appends an optional <code>actions: [{type, params, label}]</code> array to every <code>/api/chat</code> and <code>/api/articles/{id}/ask</code> response. Each action is a user-confirmed click (the LLM never acts directly). Minimum nine types: <code>navigate</code>, <code>analyze_url</code>, <code>apply_search_filters</code>, <code>apply_map_filters</code>, <code>open_methodology_section</code>, <code>open_country</code>, <code>start_deep_search</code>, <code>bookmark_article</code>, <code>start_calibration_label</code>.</p>

<h4>Impact graph</h4>
<table class=impact>
<tr class=r-blast-high><td><b>Primary edit</b></td><td><code>src/backend/app/domains/intelligence/conversation_engine.py</code> &mdash; emit structured <code>ChatActionSpec</code> alongside the answer; the LLM produces a thin JSON sidecar</td></tr>
<tr><td>Schema</td><td>New table <code>chat_actions_log(action_id, session_id, message_id, action_type, params, was_clicked, clicked_at)</code> for telemetry + provenance</td></tr>
<tr><td>API</td><td><code>api/chat_routes.py</code> &mdash; pass-through; <code>api/conversation_routes.py</code> &mdash; record click events</td></tr>
<tr><td>Prompt registry</td><td><code>intelligence/prompts.py</code> &mdash; new <code>chat_synthesis_with_actions</code> prompt (versioned, fingerprinted); the LLM is taught the 9 action shapes inline</td></tr>
<tr><td>Frontend dispatchers</td><td><code>src/frontend/src/components/AgenticAssistant.tsx</code> + new <code>chatActionDispatcher.ts</code> + 9 small adapters in <code>src/frontend/src/lib/chat-actions/{navigate,analyzeUrl,...}.ts</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Routes that need to be "deep-linkable"</td><td><code>/map?country=&hellip;</code>, <code>/search?credibility=&hellip;&amp;tag=&hellip;</code>, <code>/analyze?url=&hellip;</code>, <code>/deep-search?q=&hellip;</code>, <code>/methodology#sustainability</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Tests</td><td>9 new dispatcher tests + 1 contract test (prompt output validates against the schema with Zod / Pydantic)</td></tr>
</table>

<div class=dag>
gitnexus query:
  graph trace --from conversation_engine.py:converse --depth 5 --include frontend
expected fan-out: 3 backend modules, 2 routes, 1 prompt, 12 frontend files, 11 tests
risk class:       HIGH (LLM-driven UX state changes; needs the user-confirm-click guardrail)
</div>

<h4>Effects</h4>
<ul>
  <li>UX axis lift: largest single move identified in the UI/UX audit. Reduces friction for institutional researchers (the Professional / Enterprise tier).</li>
  <li>Telemetry side-effect: <code>chat_actions_log</code> becomes a high-quality dataset of <i>which</i> answers users actually act on &mdash; an input to calibration labels.</li>
  <li>Regulatory fit: when paired with R4 (AI Act badges), every dispatched action carries the model + prompt version into the URL state.</li>
</ul>

<h4>Risk &amp; rollback</h4>
<p>Risk: <b>high</b>. An LLM that produces malformed action params can navigate users to bad states. Mitigations: (1) every action passes through a Zod schema validator <i>before</i> being shown as a chip, (2) chips show the action label, not raw JSON, (3) <code>actions[]</code> field is optional and feature-flagged off by default. Rollback: client ignores the field; the chat reverts to read-only.</p>

<!-- =================== R3 AUDIT TRAIL JOIN =================== -->
<h3>R3. Audit-trail UUID &harr; title denormalisation</h3>
<p><b>What.</b> The <code>/api/methodology/audit-trail/{url-analysis|article|claim|deep-search}/{id}</code> endpoints currently return <code>source_article_ids</code> as an opaque JSONB array of UUIDs. An external auditor cannot follow the chain without N additional API calls. Join <code>articles</code> in the audit-trail SQL and return <code>[{article_id, title, url, source_name, source_tier, published_at}]</code>.</p>

<h4>Impact graph</h4>
<table class=impact>
<tr class=r-blast-low><td><b>Primary edit</b></td><td><code>api/methodology_routes.py</code> &mdash; four audit-trail endpoints; one shared <code>_hydrate_source_articles(ids)</code> helper</td></tr>
<tr><td>Performance</td><td>Single CTE with <code>WHERE article_id = ANY($1::uuid[])</code> &mdash; HNSW partial index already keys on <code>article_id</code></td></tr>
<tr><td>Frontend</td><td><code>MethodologyDrawer.tsx</code> renders titles as clickable links; <code>HallucinationBlock</code> attaches per-source rate</td></tr>
